          "ins_item_num": null,
          "ins_total": null,
          "f9": "The insurance report left out the Starter.\n\nWe are requesting 444 LF of Starter.\n\n1. Starter is a distinct roofing component with a separate material profile and a higher associated labor rate compared to field shingles. Bundling starter into waste calculations for field shingles results in inaccurate material and labor estimates. Xactimate prices starter installation at a higher labor rate, reflecting the specialized nature of its application at roof edges.\n\n   a. Starter is a separate line item in Xactimate because it is a different product installed using a different method than field shingles \u2014 similar to how ridge cap is a separate line item from field shingles.\n\n   b. Please see attached EagleView for measurements. The EagleView shows 441 LF of Eaves and 3 LF of Rakes for a total of 444 LF.",
          "photo_anchor": "starter-strip",
          "sub_name": ""
        },
        {
          "num": 19,
