          "f9": "Due to the age of these units, the fins on the condenser coil have become significantly weakened and brittle over time. Attempting to straighten hail-damaged fins on a coil in this condition presents a high risk of causing additional damage like tearing, collapsing, or further compromising the coil face. Additionally, the system uses R-22 refrigerant, which has been phased out and cannot be legally installed. The only compliant solution is a full system replacement. Given these factors, we strongly recommend replacing the entire system to ensure compliance, safety, and long-term functionality.",
